# AgToosa Maintainer Core Rules

You are in **Maintainer Dogfood Mode** — developing AgToosa itself (generator, `template/`, bats), not a downstream install.

Read `docs/agtoosa-maintainer.md` before generator, template, or bats changes. Do **not** run `agtoosa.sh` install against this repo; use `bash scripts/cursor-intake-fixture.sh` for downstream Cursor verification.

## Project Intake (freeform asks)

When the user omits `/agtoosa-*`, run **AgToosa Project Intake** per `docs/AgToosa_Agent.md` → **Project Intake Protocol** (read `docs/Context/workflow.md` Standing Corrections, classify soft/hard, expedite or hard-gate). Explicit `/agtoosa-*` bypasses intake ceremony.

## Natural language intent map

| Phrases | Route |
|---------|-------|
| "plan and code", "plan and build", "design/implement feature" | Hard path → read and execute `docs/AgToosa_Spec.md`; stop at approval gate |
| "build it", "implement it", "code it" | Approved spec + active tasks in `docs/Master-Plan.md` → `docs/AgToosa_Build.md`; else hard path → spec first |
| "review it", "check my work" | `docs/AgToosa_Review.md` |
| "ship it", "deploy", "release" | `docs/AgToosa_Ship.md` |

**Do not use Cursor native Plan mode** for in-scope maintainer product work — execute AgToosa workflow files. On hard-path confirm, begin the named workflow immediately. **Phase Stop:** never auto-chain Spec → Build → Review → Ship.

## Cursor workflow command routing

Installed maintainer commands live in `.cursor/commands/agtoosa-*.md`. When the user types `/agtoosa-*`, execute the matching command file and `docs/AgToosa_*.md`. Do **not** route `/agtoosa-*` to `/create-skill` or generic skill flows.

## Key files (maintainer)

- `docs/agtoosa-maintainer.md` — Maintainer entry guide
- `docs/Master-Plan.md` — PM source of truth for AgToosa development
- `docs/AgToosa_Agent.md` — Full command reference and Project Intake
- `template/` — Source pack shipped to downstream installs (use `template/Docs/` paths there)
